@startuml IC MS - Runtime Intent Sequence Flows
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #dae8fc
skinparam participantBorderColor #6c8ebf
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam noteBorderColor #d6b656
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff2cc
skinparam dividerBackgroundColor #f0f0f0
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #f9f9f9

title Intent Creation MS (IC MS) — Runtime Intent Sequence Flows

actor "External Consumer" as Consumer
participant "NGW / API Gateway" as GW
participant "Intent Creation MS\n(IC MS)" as ICMS
participant "Intent Definition MS\n(ID MS)" as IDMS
collections "Intent\nStore (DB)" as STORE
database "Outbox /\nDelivery Outbox (DB)" as OUTBOX
database "Subscription\nRegistry (DB)" as SUBREG
participant "Delivery Relay\n(background worker)" as RELAY
collections "Downstream\nServices" as DS
participant "Intent Assurance MS\n(IA MS)" as IAMS
actor "Subscriber\nListener" as SUB

== 1. Runtime Intent Creation ==
Consumer -> GW : POST /intentManagement/v5/intent\n{ intentSpecification.id, expression/request, ... }
GW -> ICMS : forward request

group Syntactic Validation
    ICMS -> ICMS : validate TMF resource shape
    ICMS -> IDMS : GET /intentManagement/v5/intentSpecification/{id}\n(verify referenced spec is Active)
    IDMS --> ICMS : IntentSpecification { lifecycleStatus: "Active", schema/definition }
    ICMS -> ICMS : validate runtime expression/request shape\nagainst active IntentSpecification definition
end

alt Validation fails
    ICMS --> GW : 422 Unprocessable Entity\n{ code: VALIDATION_FAILED, errors: [...] }
    GW --> Consumer : 422 VALIDATION_FAILED
else Validation succeeds
    group Atomic DB transaction
        ICMS -> STORE : persist external Intent projection\n{ id, version: 1, lifecycleStatus: Acknowledged }
        ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentCreateEvent row { status: PENDING }
    end
    ICMS --> GW : 201 Created { intent, lifecycleStatus: Acknowledged }
    GW --> Consumer : 201 Created { intent }

    ICMS -> DS : emit IntentValidatedEvent (internal)\n→ semantic interpretation → optimisation\n→ orchestration preparation → apply\n→ callback interpretation → assurance
    note right of DS : Downstream services process\nthe intent asynchronously

    DS --> ICMS : outcome/projection events\n(progress, fulfilment state updates)
    ICMS -> STORE : update external Intent projection\n(lifecycleStatus, IntentReport view)

    RELAY -> OUTBOX : poll PENDING IntentCreateEvent
    OUTBOX --> RELAY : [IntentCreateEvent]
    RELAY -> SUBREG : lookup matching subscriptions
    SUBREG --> RELAY : [{ callbackUrl }]
    RELAY -> SUB : HTTPS POST {callbackUrl}\n{ event: IntentCreateEvent, intentId, lifecycleStatus }
    alt HTTP 2xx
        SUB --> RELAY : 204 No Content
        RELAY -> OUTBOX : mark DELIVERED
    else failure
        SUB --> RELAY : 4xx / 5xx / timeout
        RELAY -> OUTBOX : increment retry count (delivery policy back-off)
    end
end

== 2. Runtime Intent Update ==
note over Consumer, ICMS : Unsafe operations require If-Match header (optimistic concurrency via ETag)
Consumer -> GW : PUT /intentManagement/v5/intent/{id}\n  or PATCH /intentManagement/v5/intent/{id}\nHeaders: If-Match: "{currentETag}"
GW -> ICMS : forward request

ICMS -> STORE : fetch current Intent record + ETag
STORE --> ICMS : { intent, etag }

alt ETag mismatch (concurrent modification)
    ICMS --> GW : 412 Precondition Failed
    GW --> Consumer : 412 Precondition Failed
else ETag matches
    ICMS -> ICMS : apply optimistic concurrency check
    group Syntactic Validation (same as creation)
        ICMS -> IDMS : validate updated expression against active IntentSpecification
        IDMS --> ICMS : validation result
    end

    alt Meaningful runtime content change
        group Atomic DB transaction
            ICMS -> STORE : create new runtime version (version: n+1)\nretain version history for audit/traceability
            ICMS -> STORE : update external projection to current version
            ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentAttributeValueChangeEvent { status: PENDING }
        end
        ICMS -> DS : re-admit new version through downstream fulfilment flow
        DS --> ICMS : updated outcome/projection events
        ICMS -> STORE : update Intent + IntentReport projections
    else Minor / non-content change
        ICMS -> STORE : update in place (no new version)
        ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentAttributeValueChangeEvent { status: PENDING }
    end

    ICMS --> GW : 200 OK { intent, version: n+1, newETag }
    GW --> Consumer : 200 OK { intent }

    RELAY -> OUTBOX : poll → deliver IntentAttributeValueChangeEvent to SUB
    RELAY -> SUB : HTTPS POST {callbackUrl}\n{ event: IntentAttributeValueChangeEvent }
    SUB --> RELAY : 204 No Content
    RELAY -> OUTBOX : mark DELIVERED
end

== 3. Runtime Intent Termination ==
note over Consumer, ICMS : DELETE is runtime termination, not physical deletion.\nRecord is retained for audit, reporting, lifecycle history, traceability.
Consumer -> GW : DELETE /intentManagement/v5/intent/{id}
GW -> ICMS : forward request
ICMS -> STORE : fetch Intent record (validate exists & not already Terminated)
STORE --> ICMS : { intent }

group Atomic DB transaction
    ICMS -> STORE : set lifecycleStatus → Terminated\n(retain record — no physical delete)
    ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentDeleteEvent { status: PENDING }
end

ICMS --> GW : 202 Accepted { lifecycleStatus: Terminated }
GW --> Consumer : 202 Accepted { intent }

RELAY -> OUTBOX : poll → PENDING IntentDeleteEvent
OUTBOX --> RELAY : [IntentDeleteEvent]
RELAY -> SUBREG : lookup matching subscriptions
SUBREG --> RELAY : [{ callbackUrl }]
RELAY -> SUB : HTTPS POST {callbackUrl}\n{ event: IntentDeleteEvent, lifecycleStatus: Terminated }
SUB --> RELAY : 204 No Content
RELAY -> OUTBOX : mark DELIVERED

== 4. IntentReport Projection ==
note over IAMS, ICMS : IA MS owns runtime assurance truth.\nIC MS consumes curated assurance outcomes and projects IntentReport.
IAMS -> ICMS : publish assurance outcome event\n{ intentId, assuranceStatus, metrics, ... }
ICMS -> STORE : create / update IntentReport projection\n{ intentId, reportId, assuranceStatus, timestamp }
ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentReportCreateEvent or IntentReportAttributeValueChangeEvent

RELAY -> OUTBOX : poll → deliver IntentReport event to SUB
RELAY -> SUB : HTTPS POST {callbackUrl}\n{ event: IntentReportCreateEvent / AttributeValueChangeEvent }
SUB --> RELAY : 204 No Content
RELAY -> OUTBOX : mark DELIVERED

Consumer -> GW : GET /intentManagement/v5/intentReport\n  or GET /.../{reportId}
GW -> ICMS : forward request
ICMS -> STORE : query IntentReport projections
STORE --> ICMS : [IntentReport] or single record
ICMS --> GW : 200 OK { result }
GW --> Consumer : 200 OK { result }

note over Consumer, STORE : Ordinary external consumers do NOT delete IntentReport records.\nOnly governed internal/admin purge (policy-controlled) may remove reports.

group Admin / Governed Purge (policy-controlled, internal)
    ICMS -> STORE : remove IntentReport record (policy allows)
    ICMS -> OUTBOX : write IntentReportDeleteEvent { status: PENDING }
    RELAY -> OUTBOX : poll → deliver IntentReportDeleteEvent to SUB
    RELAY -> SUB : HTTPS POST {callbackUrl}\n{ event: IntentReportDeleteEvent }
    SUB --> RELAY : 204 No Content
    RELAY -> OUTBOX : mark DELIVERED
end

== 5a. Register Hub Subscription ==
note over Consumer, SUBREG : Subscriber registers callback URL via strict TMF /hub\nor platform extension /intent/hub
Consumer -> GW : POST /intentManagement/v5/hub\n  or POST /intentManagement/v5/intent/hub\n{ callbackUrl, query/filter }
GW -> ICMS : forward request
ICMS -> SUBREG : persist { subscriptionId, callbackUrl, filter, deliveryMetadata }
SUBREG --> ICMS : 201 { subscriptionId }
ICMS --> GW : 201 Created { subscriptionId, callbackUrl }
GW --> Consumer : 201 Created { subscription }

== 5b. Retrieve Hub Subscription ==
Consumer -> GW : GET /intentManagement/v5/hub/{id}
GW -> ICMS : forward request
ICMS -> SUBREG : lookup subscription record
SUBREG --> ICMS : subscription
ICMS --> GW : 200 OK { subscription }
GW --> Consumer : 200 OK { subscription }

== 5c. Delete Hub Subscription ==
Consumer -> GW : DELETE /intentManagement/v5/hub/{id}
GW -> ICMS : forward request
ICMS -> SUBREG : remove subscription record
SUBREG --> ICMS : confirmed
ICMS --> GW : 204 No Content
GW --> Consumer : 204 No Content

@enduml